Israeli Stocks: EZchip, Melisron, Tamir Fishman Real Estate

-- B y   S h a r o n   W r o b e l
-- 
2011-07-19T14:31:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-19/israeli-stocks-ezchip-melisron-tamir-fishman-real-estate.html
Israel ’s TA-25 Index gained the most
since July 7, advancing 0.7 percent to 1,248.76 at the 4:30 p.m.
close in Tel Aviv. Investors traded about 1.27 billion shekels
($369 million) in shares and convertible securities.  The following stocks rose or fell today. Symbols are in
parentheses.  EZchip Semiconductor Ltd. (EZCH)   advanced for a second
day, climbing 1.3 percent to 123.60 shekels, the equivalent of
$35.93 a share. Jefferies & Co. initiated coverage of the maker
of network processors with a “hold” recommendation and a 12-
month share-price estimate of $39.  Melisron Ltd. (MLSR)   increased 2.9 percent to 76.95
shekels, the biggest gain since Feb. 2. The investor in shopping
malls was rated “buy” with a share-price estimate of 100
shekels in new coverage at IBI-Israel Brokerage & Investments
Ltd.  Tamir Fishman Real Estate Fund Ltd. (TFRE)   jumped 3
percent to 1.869 shekels, the highest since March 7. The
developer of property in Eastern Europe said it is in advanced
talks to issue a controlling stake in the company to Fattal
Hotels Ltd. in exchange for Fattal’s hotel operations in Europe.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sharon Wrobel in Jerusalem at 
 swrobel4@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
